\begin_layout Paragraph
Observacion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Como 
\begin_inset Formula $T\left(0-v\right)=T\left(0\right)-T\left(v\right)$
\end_inset

 resulta 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{T\left(u\right)=T\left(v\right)\iff T\left(u-v\right)=0}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Espacio nulo
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sea 
\begin_inset Formula $T\in\mathcal{L}\left(V,W\right)$
\end_inset

 definimos el espacio nulo de 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 como: 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{N}\left(T\right)=\left\{ v\in V/T\left(v\right)=0\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 Notese que 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{N}\left(T\right)$
\end_inset

 es un espacio vectorial.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Diremos que una transformacion lineal es no singular si 
\begin_inset Formula $T\left(v\right)=0\Rightarrow v=0$
\end_inset

 es decir 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{N}\left(T\right)=\left\{ 0\right\} $
\end_inset

.
